40 (4) The department shall preapprove tax credits for each preapproval application within
41 30 days and in the received order of submitted applications. Such preapproved tax credits
42 shall be in the amount of $300.00 for each preapproval application.
43 (5) In the event that an individual taxpayer applies for preapproval and the amount of tax
44 credits available for the taxable year are not sufficient to fully fund the tax credits
45 requested, the department shall deny such taxpayer's request and shall not accept any
46 additional preapproval applications from taxpayers for the taxable year.
47 (d) For a tax credit allowed pursuant to this Code section, an individual taxpayer shall
48 maintain receipts for purchases or costs relative to the eligible expenses for three years
49 following the submission of the taxpayer's tax return claiming such tax credit. Such receipts
50 shall be made available upon request for review by the commissioner.
51 (e) In no event shall the total amount of any tax credit under this Code section for a taxable
52 year exceed the taxpayer's income tax liability. No unused tax credit shall be allowed to
53 be carried forward to apply to the taxpayer's succeeding years' tax liability. No such tax
54 credit shall be allowed the taxpayer against prior years' tax liability.
55 (f) No person shall create any list of names regarding persons who have applied for or
56 have been allowed a tax credit pursuant to this Code section except for purposes necessary
57 to the administration of such credit.
58 (g) The commissioner shall promulgate such rules and regulations as may be necessary for
59 the implementation and administration of the provisions of this Code section.
60 (h) This Code section shall stand repealed and reserved on December 31, 2031."
61 PART II
62 SECTION 2-1.
63 Said title is further amended in Code Section 48-8-3, relating to exemptions from sales and
64 use taxes, by revising paragraph (85) as follows:
